==English==

===Noun===
'''bleat'''

#The [[characteristic]] [[cry]] of a [[sheep]] or a [[goat]].

====Synonyms====
*(''sheep's cry'') [[baa]], [[baaing]], [[bleating]]

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[geblaat]] ''n''
*French: (''sheep's cry'') [[bêlement]] ''m'', (''goat's cry'') bêlement, [[béguètement]] ''m''
*German: [[Blöken]] [[:de:Blöken|^]] ''n''
*Italian: [[belato]] ''m''

===Intransitive verb===
'''to bleat'''

#Of a sheep or goat, to make its characteristic cry.
#(''informal'') Of a person, to [[complain]].

====Synonyms====
*(1): [[baa]]
*(2): [[kvetch]] (''US''), [[moan]], [[whinge]] (''British''), [[whine]]

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[blaten]], [[blè·ren]]
*French: (''sheep'') [[bêler]] (1), (''goat'') bêler, [[bégueter]], [[chevroter]] (1); [[rouspéter]] (2)
*German: [[blöken]] [[:de:blöken|^]] (1,2)
*Italian: [[belare]] (1)

